  note         = {Introduced April 30, 2025 by Rep.\ Lucy McBath (D-GA) with 185 Democratic cosponsors. As of April 2026, the bill remains in committee and has not been enacted into law; enactment is contingent on a substantial shift in Democratic congressional power. Key provisions: (1) Bans import, sale, manufacture, transfer, or possession of semiautomatic assault weapons (SAWs) and large capacity ammunition feeding devices (LCAFDs) with a grandfathering exception for pre-enactment possession. (2) Appendix A explicitly exempts ``Ruger Mini-14 (w/o folding or telescoping stock or pistol grip)'' while listing the ``Sturm, Ruger \& Co.\ Mini-14 Tactical Rifle M-14/20CF'' (with those ergonomic features) in the prohibited weapons enumeration---codifying in statutory text the proposition that the regulated variable is ergonomic accessibility, not lethality. (3) Grandfathered SAWs may be possessed and transferred (with background checks); grandfathered LCAFDs may only be possessed, not transferred---a two-tier asymmetry tightening the economic foreclosure on new buyers. (4) Law enforcement officers (federal, state, campus, and retired) are exempted on and off duty. (5) Federal grants authorized for state and local buy-back programs.},
}

